Method Detail

name

public java.lang.String name(java.lang.String hint)
Creates a name according to the hint without adding the name to this collection. The name created will conform to the restrictions defined by this class. It is not guaranteed that distinct hints produce distinct names. For example, two overly long hints may become the same name after truncation. The names are distinct only when the hints are added through the add method, and the names are distinct only within this collection.

Parameters:
hint - the hint
Returns:
the name derived from the hint
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if the given hint is null
UnsupportedCharacterException - if a character in the hint cannot be used to derive the name
See Also:
add(java.lang.String)

add

public final java.lang.String add(java.lang.String hint)
Creates a name according to the hint and then adds it to this collection. A name is first created by method create. If the name already exists in this collection or in the list of reserved names, a sequence number is appended. This process continues until the name is distinct in this collection. For example, if "foo" already exists in this collection or in the list of reserved names, adding "foo" again will create a new entry "foo2" in this collection. The length of the actual entry never exceeds the maximum length allowed by this object.

Parameters:
hint - the hint
Returns:
the name added to this collection
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if the given hint is null
See Also:
name(java.lang.String)

iterator

public final java.util.Iterator<java.lang.String> iterator()
Returns the iterator for the names in this collection in the order they were added.

Returns:
the iterator for the names in this collection. The return iterator is never null. remove() is unsupported.
